Gamesa Corp. Tecnologica SA,  Spain â€™s
largest wind-turbine maker, plans to start three new plants in  India  by 2012, it said today in a statement.  The company plans to invest 5 billion rupees ($111 million)
to build the plants in Gujarat and Tamil Nadu states, the
company said. The facilities will manufacture nacelles for 2-
megawatt turbines as well as blades and towers.  Gamesa is planning 800 megawatts of production capacity in
